    },
    {
      "height": 430,
      "id": "34b8e29fc915678a",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "paradox:\nhigh barriers feel contraining, but are required for gameplay\n\nstudy:\nSuper Mario Sunshine, Super Mario Odyssey, The Talos Principle\n\nsolutions:\ninvisible walls, floating islands, teleporting the player back\n### Negative space is not all unwalkable area.",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 642,
      "x": -2280,
      "y": -6230
    },
    {
      "height": 60,
      "id": "d8916eb4cbe89255",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "lion",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 120,
      "x": -1954,
      "y": -4640
    },
    {
      "height": 509,
      "id": "40207380aa8ecbb7",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "Issue: Only two lightmaps per room supported\n\npossible solutions:\n- move four batteries to different rooms\n- make most powered areas not affect lights\n\nMonkey girl trying to fix the lights, climbing on the supports\n\nGiraffe girl \"I mean, I can *see* the problem, but like...\" clearly can't reach the battery\n\nDiscotech lit by candle light partially, but that's not enough",
      "type": "text",
      "width": 502,
      "x": -2245,
      "y": -5724
    },
    {
      "height": 340,
      "id": "a25e9cbbc0fc3adc",
      "styleAttributes": {
      },
      "text": "beach main area:\n- sprocket gate\n\t- beat-up fence, path through tropical trees\n- barriers\n\t- trees give visual barrier without being an actual barrier\n\t- parking area up top",
      "type": "text",
